div.p:
I say to these good and honest people that from the beginning of the restoration of the gospel
of the Lord, it has been known that the gospel was meant to take care of the full life of man;
and whenever they find a Latter-day Saint chapel fully completed and dedicated, they will
invariably find that there are in it classrooms and recreational facilities designed to provide
for development in all the aspects of the lives of its members—physical, social, intellectual,
cultural, as well as spiritual.
